I mean the kid LOCKED HIMSELF IN HIS ROOM for like two days or something and the mom didnt assume something was wrong.<BR>
<BR>
But she should have done something long before that. When he cried because of the game the mom didnt realize he was probably crying because of more than the game. That he was crying because he thought his life was in so much a mess his only means of escape was to let a simple thing like everquest mean more in his life than than life itself. Im sure the mom was worried about suicide but was so blinded by her selfishness to do something about it.<BR>
<BR>
The only thing she did was give words of wisdom to him like &quot;Its only a game- make believe&quot;. Did she think he took the &quot;Your in our world now&quot; on the box so seriously that he abandoned every thing in his real life. And he was going to say &quot;Oh gah mom, it all makes sense now. Im gonna cancel my EQ account now and then we can go down to the skating rink and we can start some of that son-mother bonding up again.&quot; Then she'd say.&quot; Oh sorry son... Im, uh busy tonight, maybe... some other time.&quot; Im not trying to be mean to the mother its just it would probably be true.<BR>
<BR>
And then from the payoff of all his moms ignorance and selfishness he takes everthing away with one regretable finger movement. And the mom blames it on some people that were never even aware of his existance and his pain that did just as much(Little) to help him as she did. <BR>
<BR>
What if the son somehow came back to life and asked his mom what she did after he died. What she did to recooperate(Sry for spelling just pronounce it) from that tragic moment of her life. And she would say &quot;Well son first thing I did was get rich by sueing some people have no reason to get sued. Yep son, I sucked as much money as I could from your death.&quot; THat person that said that some people have no right to become parents couldnt be more correct.<BR>
<BR>
Dawnuu,<BR>
